criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — documented growth facts/assumptions (revenue, growth levers);  
Represent/Implement — explicit 5-year forecast and scenario setup;  
Validate — sensitivity on terminal growth/WACC and tracking terminal value share.

Discover — documented specific assumptions (revenue, margins, WACC, growth levers) that feed the model; 
Implement/Represent — built and parameterized three scenarios (Downside/Base/Upside) and a 5-year forecast; 
Validate — ran sensitivity tests (WACC, terminal growth, synergies) linking assumption changes to valuation outputs; 
Evolve — compared outcome ranges (football field) and synthesized a bid recommendation.

Define & Discover — explicitly documents the valuation object (Panera) and deal facts/assumptions; 
Evolve — explicitly identifies the acquirer/stakeholder (KKR) and produces a bid; 
Define & Discover also names Management as a stakeholder in capital/rollover assumptions.
